about.summary: Generate area-proportional Euler diagrams using numerical optimization. An Euler diagram is a generalization of a Venn diagram, relaxing the criterion that all interactions need to be represented. Diagrams may be fit with ellipses and circles via a wide range of inputs and can be visualized in numerous ways.

name: r-eulerr
raw_recipe:
{% set version = '5.0.0' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-eulerr
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/eulerr_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/eulerr/eulerr_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 566a951866112e3f07198b1f12009d9a3b2eda7c4663ee562030b77c2d3a7508

build:
  # r-gensa is not available for Windows
  skip: True  # [win]
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 0
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}        # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}      # [not win]
    - {{native}}toolchain        # [win]
    - {{posix}}filesystem        # [win]
    - {{posix}}make
    - {{posix}}sed               # [win]
    - {{posix}}coreutils         # [win]
    - {{posix}}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-gensa
    - r-rcpp
    - r-rcpparmadillo >=0.7.600.1.0
    - r-polyclip
    - r-polylabelr
  run:
    - r-base
    - {{native}}gcc-libs         # [win]
    - r-gensa
    - r-rcpp
    - r-rcpparmadillo >=0.7.600.1.0
    - r-polyclip
    - r-polylabelr

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('eulerr')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('eulerr')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/jolars/eulerr
  license: GPL-3
  summary: Generate area-proportional Euler diagrams using numerical optimization. An Euler diagram
    is a generalization of a Venn diagram, relaxing the criterion that all interactions
    need to be represented. Diagrams may be fit with ellipses and circles via a wide
    range of inputs and can be visualized in numerous ways.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file: '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - johanneskoester
    - bgruening
    - daler
    - jdblischak
    - cbrueffer
    - dbast
